00:04:01.890 --> 00:04:02.510
COLT MCANLIS: Absolutely.

00:04:02.510 --> 00:04:05.190
So, Native Client is a
technology that allows you to

00:04:05.190 --> 00:04:09.560
run C and C++ code in your
web browser, as safely as

00:04:09.560 --> 00:04:11.830
JavaScript, no plug-in
required.

00:04:11.830 --> 00:04:14.400
Which is fantastic, because this
means that there's this

00:04:14.400 --> 00:04:17.720
perfect little critical point
between developers who pride

00:04:17.720 --> 00:04:19.920
themselves on reaching the
maximum amount of users

00:04:19.920 --> 00:04:23.210
running on lots of platforms but
still want the executional

00:04:23.210 --> 00:04:25.580
control and the speed required
to be able to

00:04:25.580 --> 00:04:26.830
actually execute the code.

00:04:26.830 --> 00:04:30.060
So the critical thing is that
you can actually run Native

00:04:30.060 --> 00:04:30.660
Client code.

00:04:30.660 --> 00:04:33.060
So this is C++ code, you've
got an existing code base,

00:04:33.060 --> 00:04:35.250
you've got years of development,
engineers have

00:04:35.250 --> 00:04:37.570
been trained, millions of
dollars in the code base.

00:04:37.570 --> 00:04:39.380
You can run it right in the
web browser without the

00:04:39.380 --> 00:04:42.100
plugin, which is typically where
your C++ code on the web

00:04:42.100 --> 00:04:42.720
comes in right now.

00:04:42.720 --> 00:04:45.210
And of course, most of those
you install the plugin and

00:04:45.210 --> 00:04:47.460
than all of sudden you have
like 50 new toolbar

00:04:47.460 --> 00:04:51.160
modifications to search for
gophers, and cats, and new

00:04:51.160 --> 00:04:53.090
deals on gophercat.com.

00:04:53.090 --> 00:04:55.560
So Native Client's a fantastic
technology that we have in

00:04:55.560 --> 00:04:58.110
Chrome, and we've been seeing
really good adoption with it.

00:04:58.110 --> 00:05:01.720
I think since our official
launch in December of last

00:05:01.720 --> 00:05:05.140
