00:27:31.160 --> 00:27:33.270
WOLFF DOBSON: Yes, exactly.

00:27:33.270 --> 00:27:39.040
But one of things you can do if
you develop online games is

00:27:39.040 --> 00:27:42.330
make sure that the actions that
players do, the ones that

00:27:42.330 --> 00:27:45.420
matter, actually have a round
trip to the server.

00:27:45.420 --> 00:27:49.740
That's the basic thing to do,
which also stops race

00:27:49.740 --> 00:27:50.360
conditions.

00:27:50.360 --> 00:27:52.480
You need some place that's
transactional, that players

00:27:52.480 --> 00:27:55.704
don't have an entire free access
to the entire way.

